      "question": "If a polynomial $p(x) = x^3 - 4x^2 + 5x - 2$ is divided by a polynomial $g(x)$, the quotient and remainder are $(x - 2)$ and $(-2x + 4)$ respectively. The divisor $g(x)$ is:",
      "answer": "(A)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use the division algorithm for polynomials: $p(x) = g(x) \\cdot q(x) + r(x)$.",
          "Substitute the given values: $x^3 - 4x^2 + 5x - 2 = g(x) \\cdot (x - 2) + (-2x + 4)$.",
          "Rearrange the equation to isolate the term with $g(x)$: $g(x) \\cdot (x - 2) = x^3 - 4x^2 + 5x - 2 - (-2x + 4)$.",
          "Simplify the expression: $g(x) \\cdot (x - 2) = x^3 - 4x^2 + 7x - 6$.",
          "Divide $x^3 - 4x^2 + 7x - 6$ by $(x - 2)$ to find $g(x)$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$p(x) = g(x)q(x) + r(x) \\Rightarrow x^3 - 4x^2 + 5x - 2 = g(x)(x - 2) + (-2x + 4) \\Rightarrow g(x)(x - 2) = x^3 - 4x^2 + 7x - 6 \\Rightarrow g(x) = \\frac{x^3 - 4x^2 + 7x - 6}{x - 2} \\Rightarrow g(x) = x^2 - 2x + 3$"
      },
